              <table id="EditorialReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Description:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1">A must see for anyone considering international adoption!  <P>Former TV News Reporter Rebecca Coates Nee takes you on her personal adoption journey to China. In this hour-long video, she shows you: why there&#146;s a need for adoption in China, how to choose an agency, cost estimates, requirements, the documentation process, helpful Internet resources, tips for managing the wait, how to prepare for the baby, common medical concerns, what to pack for the trip and what to buy in China.  <P>Then, see the heartwarming moment when she meets her baby and watch the adoption process in China unfold. Finally, watch how their bond develops during their first few months at home together.  <P>This video is independently produced and is not an endorsement of any agency, service or product. A portion of the proceeds will be donated to charitable children&#146;s services in China.</span>
              
</td></tr></table>
